                            <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"><font color="#1a1515" face="inter, sans-serif"><span style="font-size:18px">We’ve received a lot of questions from readers in recent months about health insurance options for aging Americans, and last week’s <em>Ask an Expert</em> about long-term healthcare myths only increased the volume of queries. So, today, we’re relying on two <a href="https://health.usnews.com/health-news/medicare/articles/medicare-vs-medicare-advantage-how-to-choose" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #f25252;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">recently updated</a> and expert-approved articles from <a href="https://health.usnews.com/medicare/articles/medicare-vs-medicaid-what-is-the-difference" target="_blank" style="mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #f25252;font-weight: normal;text-decoration: underline;">U.S. News &amp; World Report</a>.&nbsp;</span></font>
